#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:3
msgid "Using F2PY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:5
msgid ""
"This page contains a reference to all command-line options for the ``f2py`` "
"command, as well as a reference to internal functions of the ``numpy.f2py`` "
"module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:10
msgid "Using ``f2py`` as a command-line tool"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:12
msgid ""
"When used as a command-line tool, ``f2py`` has three major modes, "
"distinguished by the usage of ``-c`` and ``-h`` switches."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:16
msgid "1. Signature file generation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:18
msgid "To scan Fortran sources and generate a signature file, use"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:20
msgid ""
"f2py -h <filename.pyf> <options> <fortran files>   \\\n"
"  [[ only: <fortran functions>  : ]                \\\n"
"    [ skip: <fortran functions>  : ]]...           \\\n"
"  [<fortran files> ...]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:29
msgid ""
"A Fortran source file can contain many routines, and it is often not "
"necessary to allow all routines to be usable from Python. In such cases, "
"either specify which routines should be wrapped (in the ``only: .. :`` part) "
"or which routines F2PY should ignore (in the ``skip: .. :`` part)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:34
msgid ""
"If ``<filename.pyf>`` is specified as ``stdout``, then signatures are "
"written to standard output instead of a file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:37
msgid ""
"Among other options (see below), the following can be used in this mode:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:40
msgid "``--overwrite-signature``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:40
msgid "Overwrites an existing signature file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:43
msgid "2. Extension module construction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:45
msgid "To construct an extension module, use"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:47
msgid ""
"f2py -m <modulename> <options> <fortran files>   \\\n"
"  [[ only: <fortran functions>  : ]              \\\n"
"    [ skip: <fortran functions>  : ]]...          \\\n"
"  [<fortran files> ...]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:54
msgid ""
"The constructed extension module is saved as ``<modulename>module.c`` to the "
"current directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:57
msgid ""
"Here ``<fortran files>`` may also contain signature files. Among other "
"options (see below), the following options can be used in this mode:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:63
msgid "``--debug-capi``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:61
msgid ""
"Adds debugging hooks to the extension module. When using this extension "
"module, various diagnostic information about the wrapper is written to the "
"standard output, for example, the values of variables, the steps taken, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:79
msgid "``-include'<includefile>'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:66
msgid ""
"Add a CPP ``#include`` statement to the extension module source. "
"``<includefile>`` should be given in one of the following forms"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:69
msgid ""
"\"filename.ext\"\n"
"<filename.ext>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:74
msgid ""
"The include statement is inserted just before the wrapper functions. This "
"feature enables using arbitrary C functions (defined in ``<includefile>``) "
"in F2PY generated wrappers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:78
msgid ""
"This option is deprecated. Use ``usercode`` statement to specify C code "
"snippets directly in signature files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:84
msgid "``--[no-]wrap-functions``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:82
msgid ""
"Create Fortran subroutine wrappers to Fortran functions. ``--wrap-"
"functions`` is default because it ensures maximum portability and compiler "
"independence."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:87
msgid "``--include-paths <path1>:<path2>:..``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:87
msgid "Search include files from given directories."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:91
msgid "``--help-link [<list of resources names>]``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:90
msgid ""
"List system resources found by ``numpy_distutils/system_info.py``. For "
"example, try ``f2py --help-link lapack_opt``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:94
msgid "3. Building a module"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:96
msgid "To build an extension module, use"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:98
msgid ""
"f2py -c <options> <fortran files>       \\\n"
"  [[ only: <fortran functions>  : ]     \\\n"
"    [ skip: <fortran functions>  : ]]... \\\n"
"  [ <fortran/c source files> ] [ <.o, .a, .so files> ]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:105
msgid ""
"If ``<fortran files>`` contains a signature file, then the source for an "
"extension module is constructed, all Fortran and C sources are compiled, and "
"finally all object and library files are linked to the extension module "
"``<modulename>.so`` which is saved into the current directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:110
msgid ""
"If ``<fortran files>`` does not contain a signature file, then an extension "
"module is constructed by scanning all Fortran source codes for routine "
"signatures, before proceeding to build the extension module."
msgstr ""

