"link`` switch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:164
msgid ""
"From Python 3.12 onwards, ``distutils`` has been removed. Use environment "
"variables or native files to interact with ``meson`` instead. See its `FAQ "
"<https://mesonbuild.com/howtox.html>`__ for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:168
msgid ""
"Among other options (see below) and options described for previous modes, "
"the following can be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:172
msgid ""
"There are now two separate build backends which can be used, ``distutils`` "
"and ``meson``. Users are **strongly** recommended to switch to ``meson`` "
"since it is the default above Python ``3.12``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:177
msgid "Common build flags:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:181
msgid "``--backend <backend_type>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:180
msgid ""
"Specify the build backend for the compilation process.  The supported "
"backends are ``meson`` and ``distutils``.  If not specified, defaults to "
"``distutils``. On Python 3.12 or higher, the default is ``meson``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:202
msgid "The ``meson`` specific flags are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:209
msgid "``--dep <dependency>`` **meson only**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:205
msgid ""
"Specify a meson dependency for the module. This may be passed multiple times "
"for multiple dependencies. Dependencies are stored in a list for further "
"processing. Example: ``--dep lapack --dep scalapack`` This will identify "
"\"lapack\" and \"scalapack\" as dependencies and remove them from argv, "
"leaving a dependencies list containing [\"lapack\", \"scalapack\"]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:211
msgid "The older ``distutils`` flags are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:213
msgid "``--help-fcompiler`` **no meson**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:215
msgid "``--fcompiler=<Vendor>`` **no meson**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:217
msgid "``--f77exec=<path>`` **no meson**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:219
msgid "``--f90exec=<path>`` **no meson**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:221
msgid "``--opt=<string>`` **no meson**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:223
msgid "``--arch=<string>`` **no meson**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:225
msgid "``--noopt`` **no meson**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:227
msgid "``--noarch`` **no meson**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:233
msgid "``link-<resource>`` **no meson**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:237
msgid ""
"The ``f2py -c`` option must be applied either to an existing ``.pyf`` file "
"(plus the source/object/library files) or one must specify the ``-m "
"<modulename>`` option (plus the sources/object/library files). Use one of "
"the following options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:242
msgid "f2py -c -m fib1 fib1.f"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:246
msgid "or"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:248
msgid ""
"f2py -m fib1 fib1.f -h fib1.pyf\n"
"f2py -c fib1.pyf fib1.f"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:253
msgid ""
"For more information, see the `Building C and C++ Extensions`__ Python "
"documentation for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:259
msgid ""
"When building an extension module, a combination of the following macros may "
"be required for non-gcc Fortran compilers:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:262
msgid ""
"-DPREPEND_FORTRAN\n"
"-DNO_APPEND_FORTRAN\n"
"-DUPPERCASE_FORTRAN"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:268
msgid ""
"To test the performance of F2PY generated interfaces, use ``-"
"DF2PY_REPORT_ATEXIT``. Then a report of various timings is printed out at "
"the exit of Python. This feature may not work on all platforms, and "
"currently only Linux is supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:273
msgid ""
"To see whether F2PY generated interface performs copies of array arguments, "
"use ``-DF2PY_REPORT_ON_ARRAY_COPY=<int>``. When the size of an array "
"argument is larger than ``<int>``, a message about the copying is sent to "
"``stderr``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:278
msgid "Other options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:281
msgid "``-m <modulename>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:281
msgid "Name of an extension module. Default is ``untitled``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:284
msgid "Don't use this option if a signature file (``*.pyf``) is used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:286
msgid "Will ignore ``-m`` if a ``pyf`` file is provided."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:290
msgid "``--[no-]lower``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:290
msgid ""
"Do [not] lower the cases in ``<fortran files>``. By default, ``--lower`` is "
"assumed with ``-h`` switch, and ``--no-lower`` without the ``-h`` switch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:294
msgid "``-include<header>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:293
msgid ""
"Writes additional headers in the C wrapper, can be passed multiple times, "
"generates #include <header> each time. Note that this is meant to be passed "
"in single quotes and without spaces, for example ``'-include<stdbool.h>'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:297
msgid "``--build-dir <dirname>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:297
msgid ""
"All F2PY generated files are created in ``<dirname>``. Default is ``tempfile."
"mkdtemp()``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:299
msgid "``--f2cmap <filename>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:300
msgid "Load Fortran-to-C ``KIND`` specifications from the given file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:301
msgid "``--quiet``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:302
msgid "Run quietly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:303
msgid "``--verbose``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:304
msgid "Run with extra verbosity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:306
msgid "``--skip-empty-wrappers``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:306
msgid ""
"Do not generate wrapper files unless required by the inputs. This is a "
"backwards compatibility flag to restore pre 1.22.4 behavior."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:309
msgid "``-v``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:309
msgid "Print the F2PY version and exit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:311
msgid ""
"Execute ``f2py`` without any options to get an up-to-date list of available "
"options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:315
msgid "Python module ``numpy.f2py``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:317
msgid ""
"The f2py program is written in Python and can be run from inside your code "
"to compile Fortran code at runtime, as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:320
msgid ""
"from numpy import f2py\n"
"with open(\"add.f\") as sourcefile:\n"
"    sourcecode = sourcefile.read()\n"
"f2py.compile(sourcecode, modulename='add')\n"
"import add"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:328
msgid ""
"The source string can be any valid Fortran code. If you want to save the "
"extension-module source code then a suitable file-name can be provided by "
"the ``source_fn`` keyword to the compile function."
msgstr ""

